ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: ORANGE; 
MAN, 76, DIES AFTER BEING STRUCK BY CAR 
A 76-year-old man was struck and killed Wednesday morning while crossing Hardy 
Street. 
Dave Hill, a Police Department spokesman, said Fred Miller of Orange was 
walking eastbound across Hardy Street when he was struck by a white 1986 Toyota 
Celica. 
Miller, who suffered head and internal injuries, was rushed to United Western 
Medical Center-Santa Ana, where he was pronounced dead about 3 p.m. 
"The impact with the vehicle caused him to go through the windshield," Hill 
said. 
Hill said police questioned the driver of the car, but no charges have been 
filed. 
